 the united states  website wwwoxycom occidental petroleum corporation oxy is an american multinational oil and gas exploration and production company with operations in the united states the middle east and latin america headquartered in houston texas it is one of the largest american oil and gas companies based on  yearend market capitalization often abbreviated as oxy in reference to its ticker symbol the company is ranked on the forbes global  and fortune  list in  it was the th largest gas producer and rd largest oil producer in texas contents  history  foundation  tenure of ray r irani  appointment of vicki hollub  phibro energy trading  research in shale oil  historical financial performance  former areas of operation  california  williston basin north dakota  argentina  ecuador  brazil  libya  united kingdom  current operations  oil and gas  united states  middle east  latin america  chemical  controversies  libya  environmental record  love canal  oleum spil  colombia  caño limón  maynas carijano v occidental petroleum  political record  contributions  front group creation  gore family  safety record  piper alpha  greenmail  businesses  see also  references  external links historyedit foundationedit occidental was founded in  in california in  occidental petroleum came to the attention of armand hammer at hammers first association with occidental the company was run by dave harris roy roberts and john sullivan in  dr armand hammer was elected president and ceo in  the company discovered the lathrop gas field in the arbuckle area of the sacramento basin at lathrop over the next  years occidental expanded internationally with operations in libya peru venezuela bolivia trinidad and the united kingdom occidental won exploration rights in libya in  and operated there until all activities were suspended in  after the united states imposed economic sanctions on libya occidental entered the chemical business with the acquisition of hooker chemical company in   years after the contamination at love canal it added to its chemical industries portfolio in  with the outright purchase for  billion of cain chemical on july   an explosion and subsequent inferno on the piper alpha platform operated by occidental petroleum caledonia ltd in the scottish north sea resulted in  fatalities in what remains the worlds most deadly offshore disaster tenure of ray r iraniedit in  dr ray r irani became occidental petroleum corporations chairman and ceo he held the additional title of president from  to  occidental petroleums compensation policies came under scrutiny in  after it was announced that ceo ray irani collected  million in stock shares and salary in  in may  irani retired as ceo after the california state teachers retirement system and relational investors two major institutional occidental shareholders objected to the companys compensation policies for top executives president stephen i chazen was named ceo of occidental to replace irani since  occidental has gone from a collection of unrelated businesses to one that focuses on oil and gas during iranis tenure as ceo occidentals market capitalization increased to more than  billion from  billion by  appointment of vicki hollubedit vicki hollub who had worked at occidental since  and joined the board in  was announced to be the new ceo effective as of the  annual shareholders meeting hollub was appointed as president and ceo of occidental petroleum in april  becoming the first female to serve as chief executive officer of a major us oil and gas company in  oxy was the th largest gas producer and rd largest oil producer in texas the company ranked  on the forbes global  list in  in  it also ranked on the fortune  list phibro energy tradingedit in  oxy acquired citigroups controversial phibro energytrading business for its net asset value of approximately  million the unit was managed by andrew j hall who received compensation of approximately  million per year in  and  after the acquisition the division reported its first losses since the s in  phibro was wound down and sold research in shale oiledit starting in  occidental oil shale inc a former subsidiary of occidental petroleum began research on a shale oil extraction process the company conducted the first modified in situ oil shale experiment in  at logan wash colorado the process used explosives to create underground chambers retorts of fractured oil shale about  was mined out after which blasting was used to fracture oil shale the commercialsized retort covered  by  feet  by  m area and had height of  feet  m oil shale was then ignited on the top by external fuel and air or steam was injected to control the process as a result combustion moved from the top to the bottom of retort during the process four major zones could be identified in the preheat zone air contacted processed hot shale spent shale which preheated air in the combustion zone oxygen in air was used to burn carbon residue in the spent shale below this zone heated gas caused retorting process converting kerogen in oil shale to oil shale gas and shale oil vapors in the final zone oil and gas were cooled and collected through separation sump and collecting well all together six retorts have been burned at the site historical financial performanceedit as of december   occidental was one of the largest us oil and gas companies based on market capitalization with a market capitalization of approximately  billion occidental petroleum financial performance fiscal year market capitalization billions revenue billions income before income taxes billions                                             former areas of operationedit californiaedit occidental formerly owned  of california resources corporation the largest producer of oil and natural gas on a grossoperated barrels of oil equivalent basis in california occidental distributed  of its shares in california resources corporation to occidental shareholders in december  and distributed its remaining stake to shareholders in march  williston basin north dakotaedit in  oxy acquired shale oil properties in the williston basin in north dakota for  billion these assets as well as other assets acquired by oxy in the williston basin were sold in  for  million argentinaedit in  occidental sold its oil and gas operations in argentina to sinopec a subsidiary of china petrochemical corporation these assets included proven and probable reserves of  million  million barrels of oil equivalent × gj ecuadoredit occidental formerly operated in block  of the amazon rainforest in ecuador the government of ecuador seized the companys interest in  and in  the government agreed to pay usd million in restitution to occidental for the seizure down from the original award of usd billion the agreement was based on a  arbitration award from the international center for settlement of investment disputes icsid braziledit in  oxychem sold its investment in unipar carbocloro for r million libyaedit the companys only north african operation was in libya in  occidental and partner liwa won eight out of  exploration spots on the epsa auction making both companies among the first to enter the libyan market since the united states lifted its embargo on libya the company later began enacting an exit strategy to divest assets in the country in  united kingdomedit planning permission was granted in  for occidental petroleum to develop a site on canvey island essex for the construction of a conventional distillation oil refinery occidental refineries ltd access roads some of the tank farm a  km jetty on the river thames and a foot  m concrete chimney were built early in  occidental stopped work following economic studies which showed the refinery in the context of the opec price rises was unlikely to be profitable in  occidental noted that a  barrel per day residue upgrading refinery would be viable however no further work on the site was undertaken and the site remained derelict the tanks and the chimney were subsequently demolished only some concrete foundations and the river jetty remain extant current operationsedit oil and gasedit occidentals oil and gas operations are concentrated in three geographic areas the united states latin america and the middle east as of december   occidental had  billion barrels of oil equivalent × gj of oil equivalent net proved reserves of which  was petroleum  was natural gas liquids and  was natural gas in  the company had production of  thousand barrels of oil equivalent  gj per day united statesedit in  occidentals united states operations produced  thousand barrels of oil equivalent  gj per day representing  of the companys worldwide production this includes approximately  thousand barrels of oil equivalent  gj barrels of oil equivalent per day in the permian basin where occidental is the largest operator and oil producer and  thousand barrels of oil equivalent  gj per day of production in its midcontinent operations in colorado and south texas the  barrels of oil equivalent per day in the permian basin includes  barrels of oil equivalent per day from unconventional resources through permian resources and  barrels of oil equivalent per day using a technique called enhanced oil recovery eor eor technology used in the permian includes water flooding and carbon dioxide flooding whereby carbon dioxide is injected into underground formations to extract the oil and gas middle eastedit occidentals oil and gas operations in the middle east are in oman qatar and the united arab emirates the region produced  thousand barrels of oil equivalent  gj per day representing approximately  of  total worldwide production the region also held  of the companys proved reserves in  occidental is the largest independent oil producer in oman in qatar occidental is the secondlargest oil producer offshore and is a partial owner in the dolphin natural gas project which delivers gas to oman and the united arab emirates in early  occidental partnered with abu dhabis state oil company in developing the shah field one of the largest natural gas fields in the middle east through a joint venture known as al hosn gas al hosn gas became operational in  latin americaedit in latin america which accounted for  of total production in  occidental operates in bolivia and colombia occidentals share of production from its latin america assets was approximately  thousand barrels of oil equivalent  gj per day in  which included  thousand barrels of oil equivalent  gj per day from colombia in colombia occidental and ecopetrol the stateowned oil company discovered the giant caño limón oilfield in  it proved to be the largest discovery in colombias oil history and helped return the country to oilexporter status chemicaledit occidental chemical corporation oxychem a wholly owned subsidiary of occidental petroleum based in dallas is a leading chemical manufacturer among its interests are basic chemicals vinyls and performance chemical products oxys wholly owned chemical subsidiaries include occidental chemical corporation oxychem oxyvinyls and indspec chemical corporation oxychem manufactures polyvinyl chloride pvc resins chlorine and caustic soda used in plastics pharmaceuticals and water treatment chemicals other products manufactured by the company include caustic potash chlorinated organics sodium silicates chlorinated isocyanurates and calcium chloride oxychem has manufacturing facilities in the united states canada and chile in a joint venture with church  dwight oxychem owns armand products company which sells potassium carbonate and potassium bicarbonate in october  oxychem and mexichem announced the formation of a  joint venture ingleside ethylene llc to build a billionpound per year capacity ethylene cracker at the oxychem plant in ingleside texas along with pipelines and storage at markham texas construction is expected to be completed and the facility to be operational in  controversiesedit libyaedit occidental petroleum began operations in libya in  and operated there until us sanctions were imposed in  by president ronald reagan and was one of the first american company to resume negotiations in libya after us sanctions were lifted in  in  occidental petroleum along with five other oil companies was criticized for lobbying to exempt libya from a law written by us senator frank lautenberg dnj to assist american terror victims in seizing assets of countries found culpable in terror attacks such as the libyan bombing of the pan am flight in lockerbie in  in  the company hired hogan  hartson a washington dc law firm as its lobbyist in early  oxy ceased exploration activities and production operations due to the growing civil unrest in the country and us sanctions in june  the us securities and exchange commission sec requested information from occidental exxonmobil and conocophillips related to the libyan investment authority lia an investment firm controlled by libyan leader muammar gaddafi united kingdom prosecutors in cooperation with the sec have undertaken similar investigations of multiple oil companies during this same period to determine if there were any violations of international bribery laws the libyan investment authoritys investments were frozen by the us government in early  following the gaddafi regimes attacks on libyan civilians the company later began leaving libya environmental recordedit oxy has been noted as a leader in using carbon dioxide co flood technology or carbon sequestration for enhanced oil recovery which is a more environmentalfriendly method of oil extraction because it could stall the accumulation of carbon dioxide in the atmosphere by instead injecting it into the ground in  occidental was recognized by the environmental protection agency as production partner of the year and in  for continuing excellence  years occidental is a member of the wildlife habitat council whc the whc has certified the habitat conservation and education programs at eight of the companys sites occidental and glenn springs holdings inc a wholly owned subsidiary of occidental petroleum are participants in a large reclamation project in the southeastern united states at copper basin occidental acquired the land in  not engaging in mining activities at copper basin including the north potato creek watershed which were used to mine copper and sulfur dating back to the s in  occidental glenn springs holdings federal and local agencies came to an agreement to clean up copper basin and restore the water quality of its creeks in  researchers at the university of massachusetts amherst identified occidental petroleum as the thlargest corporate producer of air pollution in the united states with about  million pounds of toxic chemicals released annually into the air love canaledit further information love canal an abandoned parking lot near love canal in  hooker chemical and plastics began disposing chemical waste in the love canal region other companies as well as the military had used it as a chemical disposal site since the s in  hooker chemicals became the owner and the sole user of the land in  the site was filled to capacity and closed off later in the s the local school board requested hooker after threatening to resort to eminent domain sell the land the school board intended to build a school on an unused area of the dump hooker chemical leased the land to the school board in  a school was built on the site and later a middleclass residential district was built upon the land adjacent to the site the construction broke through the foot  m clay seal containing the waste in  hooker chemical was purchased by occidental petroleum in  residents became concerned about unusual health issues in the love canal region including high rates of cancer and birth defects this subsequently became a national news story and in  president jimmy carter declared a federal emergency in the area residents were eventually relocated and occidental paid  million in restitution oleum spiledit on october   an accidental spill of oleum a chemical similar to sulfuric acid occurred at indspecs facility in petrolia pennsylvania the accident caused contamination of the ventilation system and a cloud of toxic gas in the petrolia sky  residents of the area were asked to evacuate for the day colombiaedit occidental met with substantial resistance from  to  when it tried to drill for oil in the territory of the uwa people in northeast colombia the locals were concerned about environmental damage and feared that development would bring strangers and invite violence to the region there also were tribal beliefs that oil is the blood of the earth and should not be removed they believed that oil infrastructure would be a target for violent leftist guerillas in the country after years of shareholder resolutions legal battles protests and a failed test well the company abandoned the project repsol ypf took over the project and continues to work on it caño limónedit further information caño limón – coveñas pipeline on december   seventeen civilians including  children were killed when the colombian air force caf dropped a cluster bomb in the hamlet of santo domingo colombia after airscan occidentals security contractor from a private aircraft incorrectly identified it as a hostile guerrilla target groups such as farc and the national liberation army were active in the area three employees of airscan were flying the skymaster plane from which they provided the colombian military with the coordinates to drop the bombs the operation had been planned by the caf and airscan at occidentals complex in caño limón a lawsuit was attempted in april  against occidental by luis alberto galvis mujica a witness and survivor of the accident plaintiffs claims were dismissed by the trial court the dismissal was appealed to th us circuit court of appeals which sent the case back to the trial court to resolve a single issue the trial court declined to reconsider the case thereby reinstating the dismissal the case is once again on appeal maynas carijano v occidental petroleumedit on may   a group of  indigenous achuar peruvians filed suit against occidental demanding cleanup and reparations for environmental damages allegedly caused by occidental over  years the plaintiffs claimed that the company violated the industry standards and the environmental regulations by dumping a total of  billion barrels × m of toxic oil byproducts in watersheds used by the achuar people to fish drink and bathe this environmental damage was alleged to have caused premature deaths and birth defects a  study by perus health ministry tested  people in seven affected communities and found that all but two had levels of cadmium in their blood above safe levels the achuar were represented by earthrights international and the law firm schonbrun desimone seplow harris  hoffman llp on march   earthrights international eri argued to the ninth circuit court of appeals that the landmark environmental and public health case brought by indigenous peruvian achuar and the us ngo amazon watch against los angelesbased oil giant occidental petroleum oxy maynas carijano v occidental petroleum should be litigated in los angeles where oxy is headquartered the appeals court overturned the prior decision and in  the united states supreme court refused to hear the company’s arguments against a domestic trial in march  occidental petroleum made an outofcourt settlement for an undisclosed sum the funds will be used for health education and nutrition projects in five achuar communities antioquía josé olaya nueva jerusalén pampa hermosa and saukí in the corrientes river basin in peru’s northern amazon political recordedit contributionsedit occidental has disclosed its contributions to political action committees lobbyists and industry trade groups on its website in  occidental was among  entities which contributed the maximum of  to the second inauguration of president george w bush occidental also donated between  and  to the clinton foundation front group creationedit in  california resources corp created the group powering california which teamed up with the los angeles times “content solutions” team to promote oilindustry messaging the los angeles times’ content solutions department is wholly independent from its reporting and editorial staff in  as the california legislature considered extending climate policies powering california released a series of videos praising oil and attacking clean energy sources one of the videos  asserts that “renewable energy can’t replace oil”  claims wind energy is “expensive” and declares that “oil and natural gas are woven into the fabric of america” another video features interviews with paid actors touting california’s oil and gas industry gore familyedit occidentals coal interests were represented for many years by attorney and former us senator albert gore sr among others gore who had a longtime close friendship with hammer became the head of the subsidiary island creek coal company upon his election loss in the senate much of occidentals coal and phosphate production was in tennessee the state gore represented in the senate and gore owned shares in the company former vice president albert gore jr received much criticism from environmentalists when the shares passed to the estate after the death of albert gore sr and albert gore jr was a son and the executor of the estate albert gore jr did not exercise control over the shares which were eventually sold when the estate closed island creek coal was sold to consol energy in  in  the us government sold the elk hills oil field to occidental for  billion according to the government the reserve was no longer strategically necessary and the reserve was sold to reduce the national debt and the size of the government to ensure competition the field was sold in segments and offered to multiple bidders critics cited vice president al gores involvement with the company as evidence of graft safety recordedit oxychem has achieved star status under oshas voluntary protection programs as being among the safest work sites in the us piper alphaedit further information piper alpha on july   occidentals piper alpha offshore production platform in the uk north sea was destroyed when an out of service gas condensate pump was started with its pressure safety valve removed the subsequent gas leak explosion and fire resulted in the deaths of  workers in what remains the worlds deadliest offshore disaster greenmailedit in  david murdock owned about  of the companys shares when murdock called on the management to take measures to increase the share price it chose to pay greenmail to buy back shares from him at  while the market price was  businessesedit occidental oil  gas corporation occidental chemical corporation oxychem see alsoedit los angeles portal companies portal energy portal list of petroleum companies referencesedit  occidental petroleum names vicki a hollub chief executive officer press release business wire april     a b vicki a hollub at oxycom  a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u occidental petroleum corporation  form k annual report  a b  occidental petroleum forbes magazine may    a b c occidental petroleum forbes may    a b fast facts  occidental petroleum corporation  pdf oxycom    a b occidental petroleum forbes    a b texas top  gas producers  a b largest texasbased oil producers business journals august     occidental petroleum corporation history funding universe   california department of conservation division of oil gas and geothermal resources doggr california oil and gas fields volumes i ii and iii vol i  vol ii  vol iii  pdf file available on cd from consrvcagov p   la times oxy buys cain chemical deal valued at  billion  apr   duff steven  remembering piper alpha disaster bbc retrieved    douglas elizabeth april   occidental ceos  paycheck  million los angeles times retrieved no